quest_title: If a circle and a square have the same perimeter, then,
explanation_txt:
We are given that, the perimetre of the circle is equal to the perimetre of square.

Let ‘r’ be the radius of circle and ‘a’ be the side of square

\(\therefore 2 \pi r = 4 a \Rightarrow a = \cfrac { \pi r } { 2 }\)

Area of square \(\Rightarrow a ^ { 2 } = \cfrac { \pi ^ { 2 } r ^ { 2 } } { 4 }\)

and area of circle = \(\pi r ^ { 2 }\)

\(\therefore \cfrac { \text { Area of circle } } { \text { Area of square } } = \cfrac { \pi r ^ { 2 } } { \pi ^ { 2 } r ^ { 2 } / 4 } = \cfrac { 4 } { \pi } > 1\)

Thus area of circle is larger than area of square.

NOTE: Circle is plane figure whose area is maximum for a given perimeter. .

quest_title: An iron rod of volume 10\({}^{-4}\) m\({}^{3}\) and relative permeability 1000 is placed inside a long solenoid wound with 5 turns/cm. If a current of 0.5 A is passed through the solenoid, then the magnetic moment of the rod is
explanation_txt:
We know that,

\( B=\mu_{0} H+\mu_{0} I \Rightarrow I=\cfrac{\left(B-\mu_{0} H\right)}{\mu_{0}} \\ \therefore I=\left(\cfrac{\mu H-\mu_{0} H}{\mu_{0}}\right) =\left(\cfrac{\mu}{\mu_{0}}-1\right) H \)
\( \begin{align} \Rightarrow I=\left(\mu_{r}-1\right) H & = \left(\mu_{r}-1\right) \mathrm{ni} \\ & =(1000-1) \times 500 \times 0.5 \\ &=2.5 \times 10^{5} \mathrm{A} / \mathrm{m} \end{align}\)
\(\ M=I \cdot V=2.5 \times 10^{5} \times 10^{-4} \mathrm{Am}^{2} \\=25 \mathrm{Am}^{2}\)

quest_title: If the harmonic mean between \(a\) and \(b\) be \(H\), then the value of \(\cfrac{1}{H-a} +\cfrac{1}{H-b} \) is
explanation_txt:
Putting \(H=\cfrac{2ab}{a+b} \), we have

\[\cfrac{1}{H-a} +\cfrac{1}{H-b} \]

\[ =\cfrac{1}{\left(\cfrac{2ab}{a+b} -a\right)} +\cfrac{1}{\left(\cfrac{2ab}{a+b} -b\right)} \]

\[ =\cfrac{a+b}{ab-a^{2} } +\cfrac{a+b}{ab-b^{2} } \]

\[=\left(\cfrac{a+b}{b-a} \right)\left(\cfrac{1}{a} -\cfrac{1}{b} \right)\]

\[=\left(\cfrac{a+b}{b-a} \right)\left(\cfrac{b-a}{ab} \right)\]

\[ =\cfrac{a+b}{ab} \]

\[ = \cfrac{1}{a} +\cfrac{1}{b} .\]
